   69  pub enum LastPrivate {
   70      LastMod(PrivateDep),
   71      // `use` directives (imports) can refer to two separate definitions in the
   72      // type and value namespaces. We record here the last private node for each
   73      // and whether the import is in fact used for each.
   74      // If the Option<PrivateDep> fields are None, it means there is no defintion
   75      // in that namespace.
   76      LastImport{pub value_priv: Option<PrivateDep>,
   77                 pub value_used: ImportUse,
   78                 pub type_priv: Option<PrivateDep>,
   79                 pub type_used: ImportUse},
   80  }

  124  /// A NamespaceResult represents the result of resolving an import in
  125  /// a particular namespace. The result is either definitely-resolved,
  126  /// definitely- unresolved, or unknown.
  127  enum NamespaceResult {
  128      /// Means that resolve hasn't gathered enough information yet to determine
  129      /// whether the name is bound in this namespace. (That is, it hasn't
  130      /// resolved all `use` directives yet.)
  131      UnknownResult,
  132      /// Means that resolve has determined that the name is definitely
  133      /// not bound in the namespace.
  134      UnboundResult,
  135      /// Means that resolve has determined that the name is bound in the Module
  136      /// argument, and specified by the NameBindings argument.
  137      BoundResult(@Module, @NameBindings)
  138  }
  139  
  140  impl NamespaceResult {
  141      fn is_unknown(&self) -> bool {
  142          match *self {
  143              UnknownResult => true,
  144              _ => false
  145          }
  146      }
  147  }

  153  }

  155  impl<'a> Visitor<()> for Resolver<'a> {
  156      fn visit_item(&mut self, item: &Item, _: ()) {
  157          self.resolve_item(item);
  158      }
  159      fn visit_arm(&mut self, arm: &Arm, _: ()) {
  160          self.resolve_arm(arm);
  161      }
  162      fn visit_block(&mut self, block: &Block, _: ()) {
  163          self.resolve_block(block);
  164      }
  165      fn visit_expr(&mut self, expr: &Expr, _: ()) {
  166          self.resolve_expr(expr);
  167      }
  168      fn visit_local(&mut self, local: &Local, _: ()) {
  169          self.resolve_local(local);
  170      }
  171      fn visit_ty(&mut self, ty: &Ty, _: ()) {
  172          self.resolve_type(ty);
  173      }
  174  }

  210  enum TypeParameters<'a> {
  211      NoTypeParameters,                   //< No type parameters.
  212      HasTypeParameters(&'a Generics,  //< Type parameters.
  213                        NodeId,          //< ID of the enclosing item
  214  
  215                        // The index to start numbering the type parameters at.
  216                        // This is zero if this is the outermost set of type
  217                        // parameters, or equal to the number of outer type
  218                        // parameters. For example, if we have:
  219                        //
  220                        //   impl I<T> {
  221                        //     fn method<U>() { ... }
  222                        //   }
  223                        //
  224                        // The index at the method site will be 1, because the
  225                        // outer T had index 0.
  226                        uint,
  227  
  228                        // The kind of the rib used for type parameters.
  229                        RibKind)
  230  }
  231  
  232  // The rib kind controls the translation of argument or local definitions
  233  // (`def_arg` or `def_local`) to upvars (`def_upvar`).
  234  
  235  enum RibKind {
  236      // No translation needs to be applied.
  237      NormalRibKind,
  238  
  239      // We passed through a function scope at the given node ID. Translate
  240      // upvars as appropriate.
  241      FunctionRibKind(NodeId /* func id */, NodeId /* body id */),
  242  
  243      // We passed through an impl or trait and are now in one of its
  244      // methods. Allow references to ty params that impl or trait
  245      // binds. Disallow any other upvars (including other ty params that are
  246      // upvars).
  247                // parent;   method itself
  248      MethodRibKind(NodeId, MethodSort),
  249  
  250      // We passed through a function *item* scope. Disallow upvars.
  251      OpaqueFunctionRibKind,
  252  
  253      // We're in a constant item. Can't refer to dynamic stuff.
  254      ConstantItemRibKind
  255  }
  256  
  257  // Methods can be required or provided. Required methods only occur in traits.
  258  enum MethodSort {
  259      Required,
  260      Provided(NodeId)
  261  }

  362  /// An ImportResolution represents a particular `use` directive.
  363  struct ImportResolution {
  364      /// Whether this resolution came from a `use` or a `pub use`. Note that this
  365      /// should *not* be used whenever resolution is being performed, this is
  366      /// only looked at for glob imports statements currently. Privacy testing
  367      /// occurs during a later phase of compilation.
  368      is_public: Cell<bool>,
  369  
  370      // The number of outstanding references to this name. When this reaches
  371      // zero, outside modules can count on the targets being correct. Before
  372      // then, all bets are off; future imports could override this name.
  373      outstanding_references: Cell<uint>,
  374  
  375      /// The value that this `use` directive names, if there is one.
  376      value_target: RefCell<Option<Target>>,
  377      /// The source node of the `use` directive leading to the value target
  378      /// being non-none
  379      value_id: Cell<NodeId>,
  380  
  381      /// The type that this `use` directive names, if there is one.
  382      type_target: RefCell<Option<Target>>,
  383      /// The source node of the `use` directive leading to the type target
  384      /// being non-none
  385      type_id: Cell<NodeId>,
  386  }
  387  
  388  fn get<T: Clone>(cell: &RefCell<T>) -> T {
  389      cell.borrow().clone()
  390  }
  391  
  392  impl ImportResolution {
  393      fn new(id: NodeId, is_public: bool) -> ImportResolution {
  394          ImportResolution {
  395              type_id: Cell::new(id),
  396              value_id: Cell::new(id),
  397              outstanding_references: Cell::new(0),
  398              value_target: RefCell::new(None),
  399              type_target: RefCell::new(None),
  400              is_public: Cell::new(is_public),
  401          }
  402      }
  403  
  404      fn target_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace)
  405                                  -> Option<Target> {
  406          match namespace {
  407              TypeNS      => return self.type_target.borrow().clone(),
  408              ValueNS     => return self.value_target.borrow().clone(),
  409          }
  410      }
  411  
  412      fn id(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> NodeId {
  413          match namespace {
  414              TypeNS  => self.type_id.get(),
  415              ValueNS => self.value_id.get(),
  416          }
  417      }
  418  }

  437  /// One node in the tree of modules.
  438  struct Module {
  439      parent_link: ParentLink,
  440      def_id: Cell<Option<DefId>>,
  441      kind: Cell<ModuleKind>,
  442      is_public: bool,
  443  
  444      children: RefCell<HashMap<Name, @NameBindings>>,
  445      imports: RefCell<Vec<@ImportDirective> >,
  446  
  447      // The external module children of this node that were declared with
  448      // `extern crate`.
  449      external_module_children: RefCell<HashMap<Name, @Module>>,
  450  
  451      // The anonymous children of this node. Anonymous children are pseudo-
  452      // modules that are implicitly created around items contained within
  453      // blocks.
  454      //
  455      // For example, if we have this:
  456      //
  457      //  fn f() {
  458      //      fn g() {
  459      //          ...
  460      //      }
  461      //  }
  462      //
  463      // There will be an anonymous module created around `g` with the ID of the
  464      // entry block for `f`.
  465      anonymous_children: RefCell<NodeMap<@Module>>,
  466  
  467      // The status of resolving each import in this module.
  468      import_resolutions: RefCell<HashMap<Name, @ImportResolution>>,
  469  
  470      // The number of unresolved globs that this module exports.
  471      glob_count: Cell<uint>,
  472  
  473      // The index of the import we're resolving.
  474      resolved_import_count: Cell<uint>,
  475  
  476      // Whether this module is populated. If not populated, any attempt to
  477      // access the children must be preceded with a
  478      // `populate_module_if_necessary` call.
  479      populated: Cell<bool>,
  480  }

  503      }

  542      /// Creates a new module in this set of name bindings.
  543      fn define_module(&self,
  544                       parent_link: ParentLink,
  545                       def_id: Option<DefId>,
  546                       kind: ModuleKind,
  547                       external: bool,
  548                       is_public: bool,
  549                       sp: Span) {
  550          // Merges the module with the existing type def or creates a new one.
  551          let module_ = @Module::new(parent_link, def_id, kind, external,
  552                                         is_public);
  553          let type_def = self.type_def.borrow().clone();
  554          match type_def {
  555              None => {
  556                  *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  557                      is_public: is_public,
  558                      module_def: Some(module_),
  559                      type_def: None,
  560                      type_span: Some(sp)
  561                  });
  562              }
  563              Some(type_def) => {
  564                  *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  565                      is_public: is_public,
  566                      module_def: Some(module_),
  567                      type_span: Some(sp),
  568                      type_def: type_def.type_def
  569                  });
  570              }
  571          }
  572      }
  573  
  574      /// Sets the kind of the module, creating a new one if necessary.
  575      fn set_module_kind(&self,
  576                         parent_link: ParentLink,
  577                         def_id: Option<DefId>,
  578                         kind: ModuleKind,
  579                         external: bool,
  580                         is_public: bool,
  581                         _sp: Span) {
  582          let type_def = self.type_def.borrow().clone();
  583          match type_def {
  584              None => {
  585                  let module = @Module::new(parent_link, def_id, kind,
  586                                                external, is_public);
  587                  *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  588                      is_public: is_public,
  589                      module_def: Some(module),
  590                      type_def: None,
  591                      type_span: None,
  592                  });
  593              }
  594              Some(type_def) => {
  595                  match type_def.module_def {
  596                      None => {
  597                          let module = @Module::new(parent_link,
  598                                                        def_id,
  599                                                        kind,
  600                                                        external,
  601                                                        is_public);
  602                          *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  603                              is_public: is_public,
  604                              module_def: Some(module),
  605                              type_def: type_def.type_def,
  606                              type_span: None,
  607                          });
  608                      }
  609                      Some(module_def) => module_def.kind.set(kind),
  610                  }
  611              }
  612          }
  613      }
  614  
  615      /// Records a type definition.
  616      fn define_type(&self, def: Def, sp: Span, is_public: bool) {
  617          // Merges the type with the existing type def or creates a new one.
  618          let type_def = self.type_def.borrow().clone();
  619          match type_def {
  620              None => {
  621                  *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  622                      module_def: None,
  623                      type_def: Some(def),
  624                      type_span: Some(sp),
  625                      is_public: is_public,
  626                  });
  627              }
  628              Some(type_def) => {
  629                  *self.type_def.borrow_mut() = Some(TypeNsDef {
  630                      type_def: Some(def),
  631                      type_span: Some(sp),
  632                      module_def: type_def.module_def,
  633                      is_public: is_public,
  634                  });
  635              }
  636          }
  637      }

  639      /// Records a value definition.

  642              def: def,
  643              value_span: Some(sp),
  644              is_public: is_public,
  645          });
  646      }

  648      /// Returns the module node if applicable.
  649      fn get_module_if_available(&self) -> Option<@Module> {
  650          match *self.type_def.borrow() {
  651              Some(ref type_def) => (*type_def).module_def,
  652              None => None
  653          }
  654      }
  655  
  656      /**
  657       * Returns the module node. Fails if this node does not have a module
  658       * definition.
  659       */
  660      fn get_module(&self) -> @Module {
  661          match self.get_module_if_available() {
  662              None => {
  663                  fail!("get_module called on a node with no module \
  664                         definition!")
  665              }
  666              Some(module_def) => module_def
  667          }
  668      }

  670      fn defined_in_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> bool {
  671          match namespace {
  672              TypeNS   => return self.type_def.borrow().is_some(),
  673              ValueNS  => return self.value_def.borrow().is_some()
  674          }
  675      }
  676  
  677      fn defined_in_public_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> bool {
  678          match namespace {
  679              TypeNS => match *self.type_def.borrow() {
  680                  Some(def) => def.is_public, None => false
  681              },
  682              ValueNS => match *self.value_def.borrow() {
  683                  Some(def) => def.is_public, None => false
  684              }
  685          }
  686      }
  687  
  688      fn def_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> Option<Def> {
  689          match namespace {
  690              TypeNS => {
  691                  match *self.type_def.borrow() {
  692                      None => None,
  693                      Some(type_def) => {
  694                          match type_def.type_def {
  695                              Some(type_def) => Some(type_def),
  696                              None => {
  697                                  match type_def.module_def {
  698                                      Some(module) => {
  699                                          match module.def_id.get() {
  700                                              Some(did) => Some(DefMod(did)),
  701                                              None => None,
  702                                          }
  703                                      }
  704                                      None => None,
  705                                  }
  706                              }
  707                          }
  708                      }
  709                  }
  710              }
  711              ValueNS => {
  712                  match *self.value_def.borrow() {
  713                      None => None,
  714                      Some(value_def) => Some(value_def.def)
  715                  }
  716              }
  717          }
  718      }
  719  
  720      fn span_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> Option<Span> {
  721          if self.defined_in_namespace(namespace) {
  722              match namespace {
  723                  TypeNS  => {
  724                      match *self.type_def.borrow() {
  725                          None => None,
  726                          Some(type_def) => type_def.type_span
  727                      }
  728                  }
  729                  ValueNS => {
  730                      match *self.value_def.borrow() {
  731                          None => None,
  732                          Some(value_def) => value_def.value_span
  733                      }
  734                  }
  735              }
  736          } else {
  737              None
  738          }
  739      }
  740  }

  794  fn Resolver<'a>(session: &'a Session,
  795                  lang_items: @LanguageItems,
  796                  crate_span: Span) -> Resolver<'a> {
  797      let graph_root = @NameBindings();
  798  
  799      graph_root.define_module(NoParentLink,
  800                               Some(DefId { krate: 0, node: 0 }),
  801                               NormalModuleKind,
  802                               false,
  803                               true,
  804                               crate_span);
  805  
  806      let current_module = graph_root.get_module();
  807  
  808      let this = Resolver {
  809          session: session,
  810          lang_items: lang_items,
  811  
  812          // The outermost module has def ID 0; this is not reflected in the
  813          // AST.
  814  
  815          graph_root: graph_root,
  816  
  817          method_map: @RefCell::new(HashMap::new()),
  818          structs: HashSet::new(),
  819  
  820          unresolved_imports: 0,
  821  
  822          current_module: current_module,
  823          value_ribs: @RefCell::new(Vec::new()),
  824          type_ribs: @RefCell::new(Vec::new()),
  825          label_ribs: @RefCell::new(Vec::new()),
  826  
  827          current_trait_refs: None,
  828  
  829          self_ident: special_idents::self_,
  830          type_self_ident: special_idents::type_self,
  831  
  832          primitive_type_table: @PrimitiveTypeTable(),
  833  
  834          namespaces: vec!(TypeNS, ValueNS),
  835  
  836          def_map: @RefCell::new(NodeMap::new()),
  837          export_map2: @RefCell::new(NodeMap::new()),
  838          trait_map: NodeMap::new(),
  839          used_imports: HashSet::new(),
  840          external_exports: DefIdSet::new(),
  841          last_private: NodeMap::new(),
  842  
  843          emit_errors: true,
  844      };
  845  
  846      this
  847  }

  849  /// The main resolver class.
  850  struct Resolver<'a> {
  851      session: &'a Session,
  852      lang_items: @LanguageItems,
  853  
  854      graph_root: @NameBindings,
  855  
  856      method_map: @RefCell<HashMap<Name, HashSet<DefId>>>,
  857      structs: HashSet<DefId>,
  858  
  859      // The number of imports that are currently unresolved.
  860      unresolved_imports: uint,
  861  
  862      // The module that represents the current item scope.
  863      current_module: @Module,
  864  
  865      // The current set of local scopes, for values.
  866      // FIXME #4948: Reuse ribs to avoid allocation.
  867      value_ribs: @RefCell<Vec<@Rib> >,
  868  
  869      // The current set of local scopes, for types.
  870      type_ribs: @RefCell<Vec<@Rib> >,
  871  
  872      // The current set of local scopes, for labels.
  873      label_ribs: @RefCell<Vec<@Rib> >,
  874  
  875      // The trait that the current context can refer to.
  876      current_trait_refs: Option<Vec<DefId> >,
  877  
  878      // The ident for the keyword "self".
  879      self_ident: Ident,
  880      // The ident for the non-keyword "Self".
  881      type_self_ident: Ident,
  882  
  883      // The idents for the primitive types.
  884      primitive_type_table: @PrimitiveTypeTable,
  885  
  886      // The four namespaces.
  887      namespaces: Vec<Namespace> ,
  888  
  889      def_map: DefMap,
  890      export_map2: ExportMap2,
  891      trait_map: TraitMap,
  892      external_exports: ExternalExports,
  893      last_private: LastPrivateMap,
  894  
  895      // Whether or not to print error messages. Can be set to true
  896      // when getting additional info for error message suggestions,
  897      // so as to avoid printing duplicate errors
  898      emit_errors: bool,
  899  
  900      used_imports: HashSet<(NodeId, Namespace)>,
  901  }

  903  struct BuildReducedGraphVisitor<'a, 'b> {
  904      resolver: &'a mut Resolver<'b>,
  905  }
  906  
  907  impl<'a, 'b> Visitor<ReducedGraphParent> for BuildReducedGraphVisitor<'a, 'b> {
  908  
  909      fn visit_item(&mut self, item: &Item, context: ReducedGraphParent) {
  910          let p = self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_item(item, context);
  911          visit::walk_item(self, item, p);
  912      }
  913  
  914      fn visit_foreign_item(&mut self, foreign_item: &ForeignItem,
  915                            context: ReducedGraphParent) {
  916          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_foreign_item(foreign_item,
  917                                                             context,
  918                                                             |r, c| {
  919              let mut v = BuildReducedGraphVisitor{ resolver: r };
  920              visit::walk_foreign_item(&mut v, foreign_item, c);
  921          })
  922      }
  923  
  924      fn visit_view_item(&mut self, view_item: &ViewItem, context: ReducedGraphParent) {
  925          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_view_item(view_item, context);
  926      }
  927  
  928      fn visit_block(&mut self, block: &Block, context: ReducedGraphParent) {
  929          let np = self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_block(block, context);
  930          visit::walk_block(self, block, np);
  931      }
  932  
  933  }

  935  struct UnusedImportCheckVisitor<'a, 'b> { resolver: &'a mut Resolver<'b> }
  936  
  937  impl<'a, 'b> Visitor<()> for UnusedImportCheckVisitor<'a, 'b> {
  938      fn visit_view_item(&mut self, vi: &ViewItem, _: ()) {
  939          self.resolver.check_for_item_unused_imports(vi);
  940          visit::walk_view_item(self, vi, ());
  941      }

  944  impl<'a> Resolver<'a> {
  945      /// The main name resolution procedure.
  946      fn resolve(&mut self, krate: &ast::Crate) {
  947          self.build_reduced_graph(krate);
  948          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  949  
  950          self.resolve_imports();
  951          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  952  
  953          self.record_exports();
  954          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  955  
  956          self.resolve_crate(krate);
  957          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  958  
  959          self.check_for_unused_imports(krate);
  960      }

  964      //
  965      // Here we build the "reduced graph": the graph of the module tree without
  966      // any imports resolved.
  967      //
  968  
  969      /// Constructs the reduced graph for the entire crate.
  970      fn build_reduced_graph(&mut self, krate: &ast::Crate) {
  971          let initial_parent =
  972              ModuleReducedGraphParent(self.graph_root.get_module());
  973  
  974          let mut visitor = BuildReducedGraphVisitor { resolver: self, };
  975          visit::walk_crate(&mut visitor, krate, initial_parent);
  976      }

  978      /// Returns the current module tracked by the reduced graph parent.
  979      fn get_module_from_parent(&mut self,
  980                                    reduced_graph_parent: ReducedGraphParent)
  981                                    -> @Module {
  982          match reduced_graph_parent {
  983              ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_) => {
  984                  return module_;
  985              }
  986          }
  987      }
  988  
  989      /**
  990       * Adds a new child item to the module definition of the parent node and
  991       * returns its corresponding name bindings as well as the current parent.
  992       * Or, if we're inside a block, creates (or reuses) an anonymous module
  993       * corresponding to the innermost block ID and returns the name bindings
  994       * as well as the newly-created parent.
  995       *
  996       * If this node does not have a module definition and we are not inside
  997       * a block, fails.
  998       */
  999      fn add_child(&mut self,
 1000                       name: Ident,
 1001                       reduced_graph_parent: ReducedGraphParent,
 1002                       duplicate_checking_mode: DuplicateCheckingMode,
 1003                       // For printing errors
 1004                       sp: Span)
 1005                       -> (@NameBindings, ReducedGraphParent) {
 1006          // If this is the immediate descendant of a module, then we add the
 1007          // child name directly. Otherwise, we create or reuse an anonymous
 1008          // module and add the child to that.
 1009  
 1010          let module_;
 1011          match reduced_graph_parent {
 1012              ModuleReducedGraphParent(parent_module) => {
 1013                  module_ = parent_module;
 1014              }
 1015          }
 1016  
 1017          // Add or reuse the child.
 1018          let new_parent = ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_);
 1019          let child_opt = module_.children.borrow().find_copy(&name.name);
 1020          match child_opt {
 1021              None => {
 1022                  let child = @NameBindings();
 1023                  module_.children.borrow_mut().insert(name.name, child);
 1024                  return (child, new_parent);
 1025              }
 1026              Some(child) => {
 1027                  // Enforce the duplicate checking mode:
 1028                  //
 1029                  // * If we're requesting duplicate module checking, check that
 1030                  //   there isn't a module in the module with the same name.
 1031                  //
 1032                  // * If we're requesting duplicate type checking, check that
 1033                  //   there isn't a type in the module with the same name.
 1034                  //
 1035                  // * If we're requesting duplicate value checking, check that
 1036                  //   there isn't a value in the module with the same name.
 1037                  //
 1038                  // * If we're requesting duplicate type checking and duplicate
 1039                  //   value checking, check that there isn't a duplicate type
 1040                  //   and a duplicate value with the same name.
 1041                  //
 1042                  // * If no duplicate checking was requested at all, do
 1043                  //   nothing.
 1044  
 1045                  let mut duplicate_type = NoError;
 1046                  let ns = match duplicate_checking_mode {
 1047                      ForbidDuplicateModules => {
 1048                          if child.get_module_if_available().is_some() {
 1049                              duplicate_type = ModuleError;
 1050                          }
 1051                          Some(TypeNS)
 1052                      }
 1053                      ForbidDuplicateTypes => {
 1054                          match child.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 1055                              Some(DefMod(_)) | None => {}
 1056                              Some(_) => duplicate_type = TypeError
 1057                          }
 1058                          Some(TypeNS)
 1059                      }
 1060                      ForbidDuplicateValues => {
 1061                          if child.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 1062                              duplicate_type = ValueError;
 1063                          }
 1064                          Some(ValueNS)
 1065                      }
 1066                      ForbidDuplicateTypesAndValues => {
 1067                          let mut n = None;
 1068                          match child.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 1069                              Some(DefMod(_)) | None => {}
 1070                              Some(_) => {
 1071                                  n = Some(TypeNS);
 1072                                  duplicate_type = TypeError;
 1073                              }
 1074                          };
 1075                          if child.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 1076                              duplicate_type = ValueError;
 1077                              n = Some(ValueNS);
 1078                          }
 1079                          n
 1080                      }
 1081                      OverwriteDuplicates => None
 1082                  };
 1083                  if duplicate_type != NoError {
 1084                      // Return an error here by looking up the namespace that
 1085                      // had the duplicate.
 1086                      let ns = ns.unwrap();
 1087                      self.resolve_error(sp,
 1088                          format!("duplicate definition of {} `{}`",
 1089                               namespace_error_to_str(duplicate_type),
 1090                               token::get_ident(name)));
 1091                      {
 1092                          let r = child.span_for_namespace(ns);
 1093                          for sp in r.iter() {
 1094                              self.session.span_note(*sp,
 1095                                   format!("first definition of {} `{}` here",
 1096                                        namespace_error_to_str(duplicate_type),
 1097                                        token::get_ident(name)));
 1098                          }
 1099                      }
 1100                  }
 1101                  return (child, new_parent);
 1102              }
 1103          }
 1104      }
 1105  
 1106      fn block_needs_anonymous_module(&mut self, block: &Block) -> bool {
 1107          // If the block has view items, we need an anonymous module.
 1108          if block.view_items.len() > 0 {
 1109              return true;
 1110          }
 1111  
 1112          // Check each statement.
 1113          for statement in block.stmts.iter() {
 1114              match statement.node {
 1115                  StmtDecl(declaration, _) => {
 1116                      match declaration.node {
 1117                          DeclItem(_) => {
 1118                              return true;
 1119                          }
 1120                          _ => {
 1121                              // Keep searching.
 1122                          }
 1123                      }
 1124                  }
 1125                  _ => {
 1126                      // Keep searching.
 1127                  }
 1128              }
 1129          }
 1130  
 1131          // If we found neither view items nor items, we don't need to create
 1132          // an anonymous module.
 1133  
 1134          return false;
 1135      }

 1137      fn get_parent_link(&mut self, parent: ReducedGraphParent, name: Ident)
 1138                             -> ParentLink {
 1139          match parent {
 1140              ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_) => {
 1141                  return ModuleParentLink(module_, name);
 1142              }
 1143          }
 1144      }

 1146      /// Constructs the reduced graph for one item.
 1147      fn build_reduced_graph_for_item(&mut self,
 1148                                      item: &Item,
 1149                                      parent: ReducedGraphParent)
 1150                                      -> ReducedGraphParent
 1151      {
 1152          let ident = item.ident;
 1153          let sp = item.span;
 1154          let is_public = item.vis == ast::Public;
 1155  
 1156          match item.node {
 1157              ItemMod(..) => {
 1158                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1159                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateModules, sp);
 1160  
 1161                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1162                  let def_id = DefId { krate: 0, node: item.id };
 1163                  name_bindings.define_module(parent_link,
 1164                                              Some(def_id),
 1165                                              NormalModuleKind,
 1166                                              false,
 1167                                              item.vis == ast::Public,
 1168                                              sp);
 1169  
 1170                  ModuleReducedGraphParent(name_bindings.get_module())
 1171              }
 1172  
 1173              ItemForeignMod(..) => parent,
 1174  
 1175              // These items live in the value namespace.
 1176              ItemStatic(_, m, _) => {
 1177                  let (name_bindings, _) =
 1178                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues, sp);
 1179                  let mutbl = m == ast::MutMutable;
 1180  
 1181                  name_bindings.define_value
 1182                      (DefStatic(local_def(item.id), mutbl), sp, is_public);
 1183                  parent
 1184              }
 1185              ItemFn(_, purity, _, _, _) => {
 1186                let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1187                  self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues, sp);
 1188  
 1189                  let def = DefFn(local_def(item.id), purity);
 1190                  name_bindings.define_value(def, sp, is_public);
 1191                  new_parent
 1192              }
 1193  
 1194              // These items live in the type namespace.
 1195              ItemTy(..) => {
 1196                  let (name_bindings, _) =
 1197                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1198  
 1199                  name_bindings.define_type
 1200                      (DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp, is_public);
 1201                  parent
 1202              }
 1203  
 1204              ItemEnum(ref enum_definition, _) => {
 1205                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1206                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1207  
 1208                  name_bindings.define_type
 1209                      (DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp, is_public);
 1210  
 1211                  for &variant in (*enum_definition).variants.iter() {
 1212                      self.build_reduced_graph_for_variant(
 1213                          variant,
 1214                          local_def(item.id),
 1215                          new_parent,
 1216                          is_public);
 1217                  }
 1218                  parent
 1219              }
 1220  
 1221              // These items live in both the type and value namespaces.
 1222              ItemStruct(struct_def, _) => {
 1223                  // Adding to both Type and Value namespaces or just Type?
 1224                  let (forbid, ctor_id) = match struct_def.ctor_id {
 1225                      Some(ctor_id)   => (ForbidDuplicateTypesAndValues, Some(ctor_id)),
 1226                      None            => (ForbidDuplicateTypes, None)
 1227                  };
 1228  
 1229                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) = self.add_child(ident, parent, forbid, sp);
 1230  
 1231                  // Define a name in the type namespace.
 1232                  name_bindings.define_type(DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp, is_public);
 1233  
 1234                  // If this is a newtype or unit-like struct, define a name
 1235                  // in the value namespace as well
 1236                  ctor_id.while_some(|cid| {
 1237                      name_bindings.define_value(DefStruct(local_def(cid)), sp,
 1238                                                 is_public);
 1239                      None
 1240                  });
 1241  
 1242                  // Record the def ID of this struct.
 1243                  self.structs.insert(local_def(item.id));
 1244  
 1245                  new_parent
 1246              }
 1247  
 1248              ItemImpl(_, None, ty, ref methods) => {
 1249                  // If this implements an anonymous trait, then add all the
 1250                  // methods within to a new module, if the type was defined
 1251                  // within this module.
 1252                  //
 1253                  // FIXME (#3785): This is quite unsatisfactory. Perhaps we
 1254                  // should modify anonymous traits to only be implementable in
 1255                  // the same module that declared the type.
 1256  
 1257                  // Create the module and add all methods.
 1258                  match ty.node {
 1259                      TyPath(ref path, _, _) if path.segments.len() == 1 => {
 1260                          let name = path_to_ident(path);
 1261  
 1262                          let parent_opt = parent.module().children.borrow()
 1263                                                 .find_copy(&name.name);
 1264                          let new_parent = match parent_opt {
 1265                              // It already exists
 1266                              Some(child) if child.get_module_if_available()
 1267                                                  .is_some() &&
 1268                                             child.get_module().kind.get() ==
 1269                                                  ImplModuleKind => {
 1270                                  ModuleReducedGraphParent(child.get_module())
 1271                              }
 1272                              // Create the module
 1273                              _ => {
 1274                                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1275                                      self.add_child(name,
 1276                                                     parent,
 1277                                                     ForbidDuplicateModules,
 1278                                                     sp);
 1279  
 1280                                  let parent_link =
 1281                                      self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1282                                  let def_id = local_def(item.id);
 1283                                  let ns = TypeNS;
 1284                                  let is_public =
 1285                                      !name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(ns) ||
 1286                                       name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(ns);
 1287  
 1288                                  name_bindings.define_module(parent_link,
 1289                                                              Some(def_id),
 1290                                                              ImplModuleKind,
 1291                                                              false,
 1292                                                              is_public,
 1293                                                              sp);
 1294  
 1295                                  ModuleReducedGraphParent(
 1296                                      name_bindings.get_module())
 1297                              }
 1298                          };
 1299  
 1300                          // For each method...
 1301                          for method in methods.iter() {
 1302                              // Add the method to the module.
 1303                              let ident = method.ident;
 1304                              let (method_name_bindings, _) =
 1305                                  self.add_child(ident,
 1306                                                 new_parent,
 1307                                                 ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1308                                                 method.span);
 1309                              let def = match method.explicit_self.node {
 1310                                  SelfStatic => {
 1311                                      // Static methods become
 1312                                      // `def_static_method`s.
 1313                                      DefStaticMethod(local_def(method.id),
 1314                                                        FromImpl(local_def(
 1315                                                          item.id)),
 1316                                                        method.purity)
 1317                                  }
 1318                                  _ => {
 1319                                      // Non-static methods become
 1320                                      // `def_method`s.
 1321                                      DefMethod(local_def(method.id), None)
 1322                                  }
 1323                              };
 1324  
 1325                              let is_public = method.vis == ast::Public;
 1326                              method_name_bindings.define_value(def,
 1327                                                                method.span,
 1328                                                                is_public);
 1329                          }
 1330                      }
 1331                      _ => {}
 1332                  }
 1333  
 1334                  parent
 1335              }
 1336  
 1337              ItemImpl(_, Some(_), _, _) => parent,
 1338  
 1339              ItemTrait(_, _, ref methods) => {
 1340                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1341                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1342  
 1343                  // Add all the methods within to a new module.
 1344                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(parent, ident);
 1345                  name_bindings.define_module(parent_link,
 1346                                              Some(local_def(item.id)),
 1347                                              TraitModuleKind,
 1348                                              false,
 1349                                              item.vis == ast::Public,
 1350                                              sp);
 1351                  let module_parent = ModuleReducedGraphParent(name_bindings.
 1352                                                               get_module());
 1353  
 1354                  // Add the names of all the methods to the trait info.
 1355                  let mut method_names = HashMap::new();
 1356                  for method in methods.iter() {
 1357                      let ty_m = trait_method_to_ty_method(method);
 1358  
 1359                      let ident = ty_m.ident;
 1360  
 1361                      // Add it as a name in the trait module.
 1362                      let def = match ty_m.explicit_self.node {
 1363                          SelfStatic => {
 1364                              // Static methods become `def_static_method`s.
 1365                              DefStaticMethod(local_def(ty_m.id),
 1366                                                FromTrait(local_def(item.id)),
 1367                                                ty_m.purity)
 1368                          }
 1369                          _ => {
 1370                              // Non-static methods become `def_method`s.
 1371                              DefMethod(local_def(ty_m.id),
 1372                                         Some(local_def(item.id)))
 1373                          }
 1374                      };
 1375  
 1376                      let (method_name_bindings, _) =
 1377                          self.add_child(ident,
 1378                                         module_parent,
 1379                                         ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1380                                         ty_m.span);
 1381                      method_name_bindings.define_value(def, ty_m.span, true);
 1382  
 1383                      // Add it to the trait info if not static.
 1384                      match ty_m.explicit_self.node {
 1385                          SelfStatic => {}
 1386                          _ => {
 1387                              method_names.insert(ident.name, ());
 1388                          }
 1389                      }
 1390                  }
 1391  
 1392                  let def_id = local_def(item.id);
 1393                  for (name, _) in method_names.iter() {
 1394                      let mut method_map = self.method_map.borrow_mut();
 1395                      if !method_map.contains_key(name) {
 1396                          method_map.insert(*name, HashSet::new());
 1397                      }
 1398                      match method_map.find_mut(name) {
 1399                          Some(s) => { s.insert(def_id); },
 1400                          _ => fail!("can't happen"),
 1401                      }
 1402                  }
 1403  
 1404                  name_bindings.define_type(DefTrait(def_id), sp, is_public);
 1405                  new_parent
 1406              }
 1407              ItemMac(..) => parent
 1408          }
 1409      }
 1410  
 1411      // Constructs the reduced graph for one variant. Variants exist in the
 1412      // type and/or value namespaces.
 1413      fn build_reduced_graph_for_variant(&mut self,
 1414                                         variant: &Variant,
 1415                                         item_id: DefId,
 1416                                         parent: ReducedGraphParent,
 1417                                         parent_public: bool) {
 1418          let ident = variant.node.name;
 1419          // FIXME: this is unfortunate to have to do this privacy calculation
 1420          //      here. This should be living in middle::privacy, but it's
 1421          //      necessary to keep around in some form becaues of glob imports...
 1422          let is_public = parent_public && variant.node.vis != ast::Private;
 1423

 1425              TupleVariantKind(_) => {

 1429                                                local_def(variant.node.id), false),

 1431              }
 1432              StructVariantKind(_) => {

 1434                                                  variant.span);

 1437                                    variant.span, is_public);

 1440          }
 1441      }

 1443      /// Constructs the reduced graph for one 'view item'. View items consist
 1444      /// of imports and use directives.
 1445      fn build_reduced_graph_for_view_item(&mut self, view_item: &ViewItem,
 1446                                           parent: ReducedGraphParent) {
 1447          match view_item.node {
 1448              ViewItemUse(ref view_paths) => {
 1449                  for view_path in view_paths.iter() {
 1450                      // Extract and intern the module part of the path. For
 1451                      // globs and lists, the path is found directly in the AST;
 1452                      // for simple paths we have to munge the path a little.
 1453  
 1454                      let mut module_path = Vec::new();
 1455                      match view_path.node {
 1456                          ViewPathSimple(_, ref full_path, _) => {
 1457                              let path_len = full_path.segments.len();
 1458                              assert!(path_len != 0);
 1459  
 1460                              for (i, segment) in full_path.segments
 1461                                                           .iter()
 1462                                                           .enumerate() {
 1463                                  if i != path_len - 1 {
 1464                                      module_path.push(segment.identifier)
 1465                                  }
 1466                              }
 1467                          }
 1468  
 1469                          ViewPathGlob(ref module_ident_path, _) |
 1470                          ViewPathList(ref module_ident_path, _, _) => {
 1471                              for segment in module_ident_path.segments.iter() {
 1472                                  module_path.push(segment.identifier)
 1473                              }
 1474                          }
 1475                      }
 1476  
 1477                      // Build up the import directives.
 1478                      let module_ = self.get_module_from_parent(parent);
 1479                      let is_public = view_item.vis == ast::Public;
 1480                      match view_path.node {
 1481                          ViewPathSimple(binding, ref full_path, id) => {
 1482                              let source_ident =
 1483                                  full_path.segments.last().unwrap().identifier;
 1484                              let subclass = @SingleImport(binding,
 1485                                                           source_ident);
 1486                              self.build_import_directive(module_,
 1487                                                          module_path,
 1488                                                          subclass,
 1489                                                          view_path.span,
 1490                                                          id,
 1491                                                          is_public);
 1492                          }
 1493                          ViewPathList(_, ref source_idents, _) => {
 1494                              for source_ident in source_idents.iter() {
 1495                                  let name = source_ident.node.name;
 1496                                  let subclass = @SingleImport(name, name);
 1497                                  self.build_import_directive(
 1498                                      module_,
 1499                                      module_path.clone(),
 1500                                      subclass,
 1501                                      source_ident.span,
 1502                                      source_ident.node.id,
 1503                                      is_public);
 1504                              }
 1505                          }
 1506                          ViewPathGlob(_, id) => {
 1507                              self.build_import_directive(module_,
 1508                                                          module_path,
 1509                                                          @GlobImport,
 1510                                                          view_path.span,
 1511                                                          id,
 1512                                                          is_public);
 1513                          }
 1514                      }
 1515                  }
 1516              }
 1517  
 1518              ViewItemExternCrate(name, _, node_id) => {
 1519                  // n.b. we don't need to look at the path option here, because cstore already did
 1520                  match self.session.cstore.find_extern_mod_stmt_cnum(node_id) {
 1521                      Some(crate_id) => {
 1522                          let def_id = DefId { krate: crate_id, node: 0 };
 1523                          self.external_exports.insert(def_id);
 1524                          let parent_link = ModuleParentLink
 1525                              (self.get_module_from_parent(parent), name);
 1526                          let external_module = @Module::new(parent_link,
 1527                                                            Some(def_id),
 1528                                                            NormalModuleKind,
 1529                                                            false,
 1530                                                            true);
 1531  
 1532                          parent.module().external_module_children
 1533                                .borrow_mut().insert(name.name,
 1534                                                     external_module);
 1535  
 1536                          self.build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate(
 1537                              external_module);
 1538                      }
 1539                      None => {}  // Ignore.
 1540                  }
 1541              }
 1542          }
 1543      }

 1605      fn handle_external_def(&mut self,
 1606                             def: Def,
 1607                             vis: Visibility,
 1608                             child_name_bindings: @NameBindings,
 1609                             final_ident: &str,
 1610                             ident: Ident,
 1611                             new_parent: ReducedGraphParent) {
 1612          debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1613                  external crate) building external def, priv {:?}",
 1614                 vis);
 1615          let is_public = vis == ast::Public;
 1616          let is_exported = is_public && match new_parent {
 1617              ModuleReducedGraphParent(module) => {
 1618                  match module.def_id.get() {
 1619                      None => true,
 1620                      Some(did) => self.external_exports.contains(&did)
 1621                  }
 1622              }
 1623          };
 1624          if is_exported {
 1625              self.external_exports.insert(def_id_of_def(def));
 1626          }
 1627          match def {
 1628            DefMod(def_id) | DefForeignMod(def_id) | DefStruct(def_id) |
 1629            DefTy(def_id) => {
 1630              let type_def = child_name_bindings.type_def.borrow().clone();
 1631              match type_def {
 1632                Some(TypeNsDef { module_def: Some(module_def), .. }) => {
 1633                  debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) \
 1634                          already created module");
 1635                  module_def.def_id.set(Some(def_id));
 1636                }
 1637                Some(_) | None => {
 1638                  debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1639                          external crate) building module \
 1640                          {}", final_ident);
 1641                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1642  
 1643                  child_name_bindings.define_module(parent_link,
 1644                                                    Some(def_id),
 1645                                                    NormalModuleKind,
 1646                                                    true,
 1647                                                    is_public,
 1648                                                    DUMMY_SP);
 1649                }
 1650              }
 1651            }
 1652            _ => {}
 1653          }
 1654  
 1655          match def {
 1656            DefMod(_) | DefForeignMod(_) => {}
 1657            DefVariant(_, variant_id, is_struct) => {
 1658              debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) building \
 1659                      variant {}",
 1660                     final_ident);
 1661              // We assume the parent is visible, or else we wouldn't have seen
 1662              // it. Also variants are public-by-default if the parent was also
 1663              // public.
 1664              let is_public = vis != ast::Private;
 1665              if is_struct {
 1666                  child_name_bindings.define_type(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1667                  self.structs.insert(variant_id);
 1668              } else {
 1669                  child_name_bindings.define_value(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1670              }
 1671            }
 1672            DefFn(..) | DefStaticMethod(..) | DefStatic(..) => {
 1673              debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1674                      crate) building value (fn/static) {}", final_ident);
 1675              child_name_bindings.define_value(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1676            }
 1677            DefTrait(def_id) => {
 1678                debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1679                        crate) building type {}", final_ident);
 1680  
 1681                // If this is a trait, add all the method names
 1682                // to the trait info.
 1683  
 1684                let method_def_ids =
 1685                  csearch::get_trait_method_def_ids(&self.session.cstore, def_id);
 1686                let mut interned_method_names = HashSet::new();
 1687                for &method_def_id in method_def_ids.iter() {
 1688                    let (method_name, explicit_self) =
 1689                        csearch::get_method_name_and_explicit_self(&self.session.cstore,
 1690                                                                   method_def_id);
 1691  
 1692                    debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1693                            external crate) ... adding \
 1694                            trait method '{}'",
 1695                           token::get_ident(method_name));
 1696  
 1697                    // Add it to the trait info if not static.
 1698                    if explicit_self != SelfStatic {
 1699                        interned_method_names.insert(method_name.name);
 1700                    }
 1701                    if is_exported {
 1702                        self.external_exports.insert(method_def_id);
 1703                    }
 1704                }
 1705                for name in interned_method_names.iter() {
 1706                    let mut method_map = self.method_map.borrow_mut();
 1707                    if !method_map.contains_key(name) {
 1708                        method_map.insert(*name, HashSet::new());
 1709                    }
 1710                    match method_map.find_mut(name) {
 1711                        Some(s) => { s.insert(def_id); },
 1712                        _ => fail!("can't happen"),
 1713                    }
 1714                }
 1715  
 1716                child_name_bindings.define_type(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1717  
 1718                // Define a module if necessary.
 1719                let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1720                child_name_bindings.set_module_kind(parent_link,
 1721                                                    Some(def_id),
 1722                                                    TraitModuleKind,
 1723                                                    true,
 1724                                                    is_public,
 1725                                                    DUMMY_SP)
 1726            }
 1727            DefTy(_) => {
 1728                debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1729                        crate) building type {}", final_ident);
 1730  
 1731                child_name_bindings.define_type(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1732            }
 1733            DefStruct(def_id) => {
 1734              debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1735                      crate) building type and value for {}",
 1736                     final_ident);
 1737              child_name_bindings.define_type(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1738              if csearch::get_struct_fields(&self.session.cstore, def_id).len() == 0 {
 1739                  child_name_bindings.define_value(def, DUMMY_SP, is_public);
 1740              }
 1741              self.structs.insert(def_id);
 1742            }
 1743            DefMethod(..) => {
 1744                debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) \
 1745                        ignoring {:?}", def);
 1746                // Ignored; handled elsewhere.
 1747            }
 1748            DefArg(..) | DefLocal(..) | DefPrimTy(..) |
 1749            DefTyParam(..) | DefBinding(..) |
 1750            DefUse(..) | DefUpvar(..) | DefRegion(..) |
 1751            DefTyParamBinder(..) | DefLabel(..) | DefSelfTy(..) => {
 1752              fail!("didn't expect `{:?}`", def);
 1753            }
 1754          }
 1755      }

 1757      /// Builds the reduced graph for a single item in an external crate.
 1758      fn build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate_def(&mut self,
 1759                                                    root: @Module,
 1760                                                    def_like: DefLike,
 1761                                                    ident: Ident,
 1762                                                    visibility: Visibility) {
 1763          match def_like {
 1764              DlDef(def) => {
 1765                  // Add the new child item, if necessary.
 1766                  match def {
 1767                      DefForeignMod(def_id) => {
 1768                          // Foreign modules have no names. Recur and populate
 1769                          // eagerly.
 1770                          csearch::each_child_of_item(&self.session.cstore,
 1771                                                      def_id,
 1772                                                      |def_like,
 1773                                                       child_ident,
 1774                                                       vis| {

 1776                                  root,
 1777                                  def_like,
 1778                                  child_ident,
 1779                                  vis)
 1780                          });
 1781                      }
 1782                      _ => {
 1783                          let (child_name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1784                              self.add_child(ident,
 1785                                             ModuleReducedGraphParent(root),
 1786                                             OverwriteDuplicates,
 1787                                             DUMMY_SP);
 1788  
 1789                          self.handle_external_def(def,
 1790                                                   visibility,
 1791                                                   child_name_bindings,
 1792                                                   token::get_ident(ident).get(),
 1793                                                   ident,
 1794                                                   new_parent);
 1795                      }
 1796                  }
 1797              }
 1798              DlImpl(def) => {
 1799                  // We only process static methods of impls here.
 1800                  match csearch::get_type_name_if_impl(&self.session.cstore, def) {
 1801                      None => {}
 1802                      Some(final_ident) => {
 1803                          let static_methods_opt =
 1804                              csearch::get_static_methods_if_impl(&self.session.cstore, def);
 1805                          match static_methods_opt {
 1806                              Some(ref static_methods) if
 1807                                  static_methods.len() >= 1 => {
 1808                                  debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1809                                          external crate) processing \
 1810                                          static methods for type name {}",
 1811                                          token::get_ident(final_ident));
 1812  
 1813                                  let (child_name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1814                                      self.add_child(
 1815                                          final_ident,
 1816                                          ModuleReducedGraphParent(root),
 1817                                          OverwriteDuplicates,
 1818                                          DUMMY_SP);
 1819  
 1820                                  // Process the static methods. First,
 1821                                  // create the module.
 1822                                  let type_module;
 1823                                  let type_def = child_name_bindings.type_def.borrow().clone();
 1824                                  match type_def {
 1825                                      Some(TypeNsDef {
 1826                                          module_def: Some(module_def),
 1827                                          ..
 1828                                      }) => {
 1829                                          // We already have a module. This
 1830                                          // is OK.
 1831                                          type_module = module_def;
 1832  
 1833                                          // Mark it as an impl module if
 1834                                          // necessary.
 1835                                          type_module.kind.set(ImplModuleKind);
 1836                                      }
 1837                                      Some(_) | None => {
 1838                                          let parent_link =
 1839                                              self.get_parent_link(new_parent,
 1840                                                                   final_ident);
 1841                                          child_name_bindings.define_module(
 1842                                              parent_link,
 1843                                              Some(def),
 1844                                              ImplModuleKind,
 1845                                              true,
 1846                                              true,
 1847                                              DUMMY_SP);
 1848                                          type_module =
 1849                                              child_name_bindings.
 1850                                                  get_module();
 1851                                      }
 1852                                  }
 1853  
 1854                                  // Add each static method to the module.
 1855                                  let new_parent =
 1856                                      ModuleReducedGraphParent(type_module);
 1857                                  for static_method_info in
 1858                                          static_methods.iter() {

 1945      /// Creates and adds an import directive to the given module.
 1946      fn build_import_directive(&mut self,
 1947                                module_: @Module,
 1948                                module_path: Vec<Ident> ,
 1949                                subclass: @ImportDirectiveSubclass,
 1950                                span: Span,
 1951                                id: NodeId,
 1952                                is_public: bool) {
 1953          let directive = @ImportDirective::new(module_path,
 1954                                                subclass, span, id,
 1955                                                is_public);
 1956          module_.imports.borrow_mut().push(directive);
 1957          // Bump the reference count on the name. Or, if this is a glob, set
 1958          // the appropriate flag.
 1959  
 1960          match *subclass {
 1961              SingleImport(target, _) => {
 1962                  debug!("(building import directive) building import \
 1963                          directive: {}::{}",
 1964                         self.idents_to_str(directive.module_path.as_slice()),
 1965                         token::get_ident(target));
 1966  
 1967                  let mut import_resolutions = module_.import_resolutions
 1968                                                      .borrow_mut();

 1970                      Some(&resolution) => {
 1971                          debug!("(building import directive) bumping \
 1972                                  reference");
 1973                          resolution.outstanding_references.set(
 1974                              resolution.outstanding_references.get() + 1);
 1975  
 1976                          // the source of this name is different now
 1977                          resolution.type_id.set(id);
 1978                          resolution.value_id.set(id);
 1979                      }
 1980                      None => {
 1981                          debug!("(building import directive) creating new");
 1982                          let resolution = @ImportResolution::new(id, is_public);
 1983                          resolution.outstanding_references.set(1);
 1984                          import_resolutions.insert(target.name, resolution);
 1985                      }
 1986                  }
 1987              }
 1988              GlobImport => {
 1989                  // Set the glob flag. This tells us that we don't know the
 1990                  // module's exports ahead of time.

 1992                  module_.glob_count.set(module_.glob_count.get() + 1);
 1993              }
 1994          }

 1998  
 1999      // Import resolution
 2000      //
 2001      // This is a fixed-point algorithm. We resolve imports until our efforts
 2002      // are stymied by an unresolved import; then we bail out of the current
 2003      // module and continue. We terminate successfully once no more imports
 2004      // remain or unsuccessfully when no forward progress in resolving imports
 2005      // is made.
 2006  
 2007      /// Resolves all imports for the crate. This method performs the fixed-
 2008      /// point iteration.
 2009      fn resolve_imports(&mut self) {
 2010          let mut i = 0;
 2011          let mut prev_unresolved_imports = 0;
 2012          loop {
 2013              debug!("(resolving imports) iteration {}, {} imports left",
 2014                     i, self.unresolved_imports);
 2015  
 2016              let module_root = self.graph_root.get_module();
 2017              self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(module_root);
 2018  
 2019              if self.unresolved_imports == 0 {
 2020                  debug!("(resolving imports) success");
 2021                  break;
 2022              }
 2023  
 2024              if self.unresolved_imports == prev_unresolved_imports {
 2025                  self.report_unresolved_imports(module_root);
 2026                  break;
 2027              }
 2028  
 2029              i += 1;
 2030              prev_unresolved_imports = self.unresolved_imports;
 2031          }
 2032      }

 2034      /// Attempts to resolve imports for the given module and all of its
 2035      /// submodules.
 2036      fn resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(&mut self,
 2037                                                module_: @Module) {
 2038          debug!("(resolving imports for module subtree) resolving {}",
 2039                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2040          self.resolve_imports_for_module(module_);
 2041  
 2042          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 2043          for (_, &child_node) in module_.children.borrow().iter() {
 2044              match child_node.get_module_if_available() {
 2045                  None => {
 2046                      // Nothing to do.
 2047                  }
 2048                  Some(child_module) => {
 2049                      self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 2050                  }
 2051              }
 2052          }
 2053  
 2054          for (_, &child_module) in module_.anonymous_children.borrow().iter() {
 2055              self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 2056          }
 2057      }

 2059      /// Attempts to resolve imports for the given module only.
 2060      fn resolve_imports_for_module(&mut self, module: @Module) {
 2061          if module.all_imports_resolved() {
 2062              debug!("(resolving imports for module) all imports resolved for \
 2063                     {}",
 2064                     self.module_to_str(module));
 2065              return;
 2066          }
 2067

 2070          while module.resolved_import_count.get() < import_count {
 2071              let import_index = module.resolved_import_count.get();
 2072              let import_directive = *imports.get(import_index);
 2073              match self.resolve_import_for_module(module, import_directive) {
 2074                  Failed => {
 2075                      // We presumably emitted an error. Continue.
 2076                      let msg = format!("failed to resolve import `{}`",
 2077                                     self.import_path_to_str(
 2078                                         import_directive.module_path
 2079                                                         .as_slice(),
 2080                                         *import_directive.subclass));
 2081                      self.resolve_error(import_directive.span, msg);
 2082                  }
 2083                  Indeterminate => {
 2084                      // Bail out. We'll come around next time.
 2085                      break;
 2086                  }
 2087                  Success(()) => {
 2088                      // Good. Continue.
 2089                  }
 2090              }
 2091  
 2092              module.resolved_import_count
 2093                    .set(module.resolved_import_count.get() + 1);
 2094          }
 2095      }

 2143      /// Attempts to resolve the given import. The return value indicates
 2144      /// failure if we're certain the name does not exist, indeterminate if we
 2145      /// don't know whether the name exists at the moment due to other

 2147      /// If successful, the resolved bindings are written into the module.
 2148      fn resolve_import_for_module(&mut self,
 2149                                   module_: @Module,
 2150                                   import_directive: @ImportDirective)
 2151                                   -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2152          let mut resolution_result = Failed;
 2153          let module_path = &import_directive.module_path;

 2156                  `{}`",
 2157                 self.idents_to_str(module_path.as_slice()),

 2162              // Use the crate root.

 2166                                             module_path.as_slice(),
 2167                                             DontUseLexicalScope,
 2168                                             import_directive.span,
 2169                                             ImportSearch) {
 2170  
 2171                  Failed => None,
 2172                  Indeterminate => {
 2173                      resolution_result = Indeterminate;
 2174                      None
 2175                  }

 2177              }
 2178          };
 2179

 2181              None => {}
 2182              Some((containing_module, lp)) => {
 2183                  // We found the module that the target is contained
 2184                  // within. Attempt to resolve the import within it.
 2185  
 2186                  match *import_directive.subclass {
 2187                      SingleImport(target, source) => {
 2188                          resolution_result =
 2189                              self.resolve_single_import(module_,
 2190                                                         containing_module,
 2191                                                         target,
 2192                                                         source,
 2193                                                         import_directive,
 2194                                                         lp);
 2195                      }

 2197                          resolution_result =
 2198                              self.resolve_glob_import(module_,

 2200                                                       import_directive.id,
 2201                                                       import_directive.is_public,
 2202                                                       lp);
 2203                      }
 2204                  }
 2205              }
 2206          }
 2207

 2210              Success(()) => {

 2212                  self.unresolved_imports -= 1;
 2213              }

 2218

 2226                  GlobImport => {

 2284              None => {
 2285                  // Continue.

 2295                  }

 2317                  // module.

 2327  
 2328                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
