 2333                          }
 2334                      }
 2335                      Some(import_resolution)
 2336                              if import_resolution.outstanding_references.get()
 2337                                  == 0 => {
 2338  
 2339                          fn get_binding(this: &mut Resolver,
 2340                                         import_resolution: @ImportResolution,
 2341                                         namespace: Namespace)
 2342                                      -> NamespaceResult {
 2343  
 2344                              // Import resolutions must be declared with "pub"
 2345                              // in order to be exported.
 2346                              if !import_resolution.is_public.get() {
 2347                                  return UnboundResult;
 2348                              }
 2349  
 2350                              match (*import_resolution).
 2351                                      target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 2352                                  None => {
 2353                                      return UnboundResult;
 2354                                  }
 2355                                  Some(target) => {
 2356                                      let id = import_resolution.id(namespace);
 2357                                      this.used_imports.insert((id, namespace));
 2358                                      return BoundResult(target.target_module,
 2359                                                         target.bindings);
 2360                                  }
 2361                              }
 2362                          }
 2363  
 2364                          // The name is an import which has been fully
 2365                          // resolved. We can, therefore, just follow it.
 2366                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
 2367                              value_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2368                                                         ValueNS);
 2369                              value_used_reexport = import_resolution.is_public.get();
 2370                          }
 2371                          if type_result.is_unknown() {
 2372                              type_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2373                                                        TypeNS);
 2374                              type_used_reexport = import_resolution.is_public.get();
 2375                          }
 2376  
 2377                      }
 2378                      Some(_) => {
 2379                          // The import is unresolved. Bail out.
 2380                          debug!("(resolving single import) unresolved import; \
 2381                                  bailing out");
 2382                          return Indeterminate;
 2383                      }
 2384                  }
 2385              }
 2386          }
 2387  
 2388          // If we didn't find a result in the type namespace, search the
 2389          // external modules.
 2390          let mut value_used_public = false;
 2391          let mut type_used_public = false;
 2392          match type_result {
 2393              BoundResult(..) => {}
 2394              _ => {
 2395                  match containing_module.external_module_children.borrow_mut()
 2396                                         .find_copy(&source.name) {
 2397                      None => {} // Continue.
 2398                      Some(module) => {
 2399                          let name_bindings =
 2400                              @Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(
 2401                                  module);
 2402                          type_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2403                                                    name_bindings);
 2404                          type_used_public = true;
 2405                      }
 2406                  }
 2407              }
 2408          }
 2409  
 2410          // We've successfully resolved the import. Write the results in.
 2411          let import_resolution = {
 2412              let import_resolutions = module_.import_resolutions.borrow();
 2413              assert!(import_resolutions.contains_key(&target.name));
 2414              import_resolutions.get_copy(&target.name)
 2415          };
 2416  
 2417          match value_result {
 2418              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2419                  debug!("(resolving single import) found value target");
 2420                  *import_resolution.value_target.borrow_mut() =
 2421                      Some(Target::new(target_module, name_bindings));
 2422                  import_resolution.value_id.set(directive.id);
 2423                  value_used_public = name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(ValueNS);
 2424              }
 2425              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2426              UnknownResult => {
 2427                  fail!("value result should be known at this point");
 2428              }
 2429          }
 2430          match type_result {
 2431              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2432                  debug!("(resolving single import) found type target: {:?}",
 2433                         { name_bindings.type_def.borrow().clone().unwrap().type_def });
 2434                  *import_resolution.type_target.borrow_mut() =
 2435                      Some(Target::new(target_module, name_bindings));
 2436                  import_resolution.type_id.set(directive.id);
 2437                  type_used_public = name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(TypeNS);
 2438              }
 2439              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2440              UnknownResult => {
 2441                  fail!("type result should be known at this point");
 2442              }
 2443          }
 2444  
 2445          if import_resolution.value_target.borrow().is_none() &&
 2446             import_resolution.type_target.borrow().is_none() {
 2447              let msg = format!("unresolved import: there is no \
 2448                                 `{}` in `{}`",
 2449                                token::get_ident(source),
 2450                                self.module_to_str(containing_module));

 2452              return Failed;
 2453          }
 2454          let value_used_public = value_used_reexport || value_used_public;
 2455          let type_used_public = type_used_reexport || type_used_public;
 2456  
 2457          assert!(import_resolution.outstanding_references.get() >= 1);
 2458          import_resolution.outstanding_references.set(
 2459              import_resolution.outstanding_references.get() - 1);
 2460  
 2461          // record what this import resolves to for later uses in documentation,
 2462          // this may resolve to either a value or a type, but for documentation
 2463          // purposes it's good enough to just favor one over the other.
 2464          let value_private = match *import_resolution.value_target.borrow() {
 2465              Some(target) => {
 2466                  let def = target.bindings.def_for_namespace(ValueNS).unwrap();
 2467                  self.def_map.borrow_mut().insert(directive.id, def);
 2468                  let did = def_id_of_def(def);
 2469                  if value_used_public {Some(lp)} else {Some(DependsOn(did))}
 2470              },
 2471              // AllPublic here and below is a dummy value, it should never be used because
 2472              // _exists is false.
 2473              None => None,
 2474          };
 2475          let type_private = match *import_resolution.type_target.borrow() {
 2476              Some(target) => {
 2477                  let def = target.bindings.def_for_namespace(TypeNS).unwrap();
 2478                  self.def_map.borrow_mut().insert(directive.id, def);
 2479                  let did = def_id_of_def(def);
 2480                  if type_used_public {Some(lp)} else {Some(DependsOn(did))}
 2481              },
 2482              None => None,
 2483          };
 2484  
 2485          self.last_private.insert(directive.id, LastImport{value_priv: value_private,
 2486                                                            value_used: Used,
 2487                                                            type_priv: type_private,
 2488                                                            type_used: Used});
 2489  
 2490          debug!("(resolving single import) successfully resolved import");
 2491          return Success(());
 2492      }

 2494      // Resolves a glob import. Note that this function cannot fail; it either
 2495      // succeeds or bails out (as importing * from an empty module or a module
 2496      // that exports nothing is valid).
 2497      fn resolve_glob_import(&mut self,
 2498                             module_: @Module,
 2499                             containing_module: @Module,
 2500                             id: NodeId,
 2501                             is_public: bool,
 2502                             lp: LastPrivate)
 2503                             -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2504          // This function works in a highly imperative manner; it eagerly adds
 2505          // everything it can to the list of import resolutions of the module
 2506          // node.
 2507          debug!("(resolving glob import) resolving glob import {}", id);
 2508  
 2509          // We must bail out if the node has unresolved imports of any kind
 2510          // (including globs).
 2511          if !(*containing_module).all_imports_resolved() {
 2512              debug!("(resolving glob import) target module has unresolved \
 2513                      imports; bailing out");
 2514              return Indeterminate;
 2515          }
 2516  
 2517          assert_eq!(containing_module.glob_count.get(), 0);
 2518  
 2519          // Add all resolved imports from the containing module.
 2520          let import_resolutions = containing_module.import_resolutions
 2521                                                    .borrow();
 2522          for (ident, target_import_resolution) in import_resolutions.iter() {
 2523              debug!("(resolving glob import) writing module resolution \
 2524                      {:?} into `{}`",
 2525                     target_import_resolution.type_target.borrow().is_none(),
 2526                     self.module_to_str(module_));
 2527  
 2528              if !target_import_resolution.is_public.get() {
 2529                  debug!("(resolving glob import) nevermind, just kidding");
 2530                  continue
 2531              }
 2532  
 2533              // Here we merge two import resolutions.
 2534              let mut import_resolutions = module_.import_resolutions.borrow_mut();
 2535              match import_resolutions.find(ident) {
 2536                  None => {
 2537                      // Simple: just copy the old import resolution.
 2538                      let new_import_resolution =
 2539                          @ImportResolution::new(id, is_public);
 2540                      *new_import_resolution.value_target.borrow_mut() =
 2541                          get(&target_import_resolution.value_target);
 2542                      *new_import_resolution.type_target.borrow_mut() =
 2543                          get(&target_import_resolution.type_target);
 2544  
 2545                      import_resolutions.insert
 2546                          (*ident, new_import_resolution);
 2547                  }
 2548                  Some(&dest_import_resolution) => {
 2549                      // Merge the two import resolutions at a finer-grained
 2550                      // level.
 2551  
 2552                      match *target_import_resolution.value_target.borrow() {
 2553                          None => {
 2554                              // Continue.
 2555                          }
 2556                          Some(value_target) => {
 2557                              *dest_import_resolution.value_target.borrow_mut() = Some(value_target);
 2558                          }
 2559                      }
 2560                      match *target_import_resolution.type_target.borrow() {
 2561                          None => {
 2562                              // Continue.
 2563                          }
 2564                          Some(type_target) => {
 2565                              *dest_import_resolution.type_target.borrow_mut() = Some(type_target);
 2566                          }
 2567                      }
 2568                      dest_import_resolution.is_public.set(is_public);
 2569                  }
 2570              }
 2571          }
 2572  
 2573          // Add all children from the containing module.
 2574          self.populate_module_if_necessary(containing_module);
 2575  
 2576          for (&name, name_bindings) in containing_module.children
 2577                                                         .borrow().iter() {
 2578              self.merge_import_resolution(module_, containing_module,
 2579                                           id, is_public,
 2580                                           name, *name_bindings);
 2581          }
 2582  
 2583          // Add external module children from the containing module.
 2584          for (&name, module) in containing_module.external_module_children
 2585                                                  .borrow().iter() {
 2586              let name_bindings =
 2587                  @Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(*module);
 2588              self.merge_import_resolution(module_, containing_module,
 2589                                           id, is_public,
 2590                                           name, name_bindings);
 2591          }
 2592  
 2593          // Record the destination of this import
 2594          match containing_module.def_id.get() {
 2595              Some(did) => {
 2596                  self.def_map.borrow_mut().insert(id, DefMod(did));
 2597                  self.last_private.insert(id, lp);
 2598              }
 2599              None => {}
 2600          }
 2601  
 2602          debug!("(resolving glob import) successfully resolved import");
 2603          return Success(());
 2604      }

 2606      fn merge_import_resolution(&mut self,
 2607                                 module_: @Module,
 2608                                 containing_module: @Module,
 2609                                 id: NodeId,
 2610                                 is_public: bool,
 2611                                 name: Name,
 2612                                 name_bindings: @NameBindings) {
 2613          let dest_import_resolution;
 2614          let mut import_resolutions = module_.import_resolutions.borrow_mut();
 2615          match import_resolutions.find(&name) {
 2616              None => {
 2617                  // Create a new import resolution from this child.
 2618                  dest_import_resolution =
 2619                      @ImportResolution::new(id, is_public);
 2620                  import_resolutions.insert(name,
 2621                                                  dest_import_resolution);
 2622              }
 2623              Some(&existing_import_resolution) => {
 2624                  dest_import_resolution = existing_import_resolution;
 2625              }
 2626          }
 2627  
 2628          debug!("(resolving glob import) writing resolution `{}` in `{}` \
 2629                 to `{}`",
 2630                 token::get_name(name).get().to_str(),
 2631                 self.module_to_str(containing_module),
 2632                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2633  
 2634          // Merge the child item into the import resolution.
 2635          if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(ValueNS) {
 2636              debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for value target");
 2637              *dest_import_resolution.value_target.borrow_mut() =
 2638                  Some(Target::new(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2639              dest_import_resolution.value_id.set(id);
 2640          }
 2641          if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(TypeNS) {
 2642              debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for type target");
 2643              *dest_import_resolution.type_target.borrow_mut() =
 2644                  Some(Target::new(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2645              dest_import_resolution.type_id.set(id);
 2646          }
 2647          dest_import_resolution.is_public.set(is_public);
 2648      }
 2649  
 2650      /// Resolves the given module path from the given root `module_`.
 2651      fn resolve_module_path_from_root(&mut self,
 2652                                       module_: @Module,
 2653                                       module_path: &[Ident],
 2654                                       index: uint,
 2655                                       span: Span,
 2656                                       name_search_type: NameSearchType,
 2657                                       lp: LastPrivate)
 2658                                  -> ResolveResult<(@Module, LastPrivate)> {
 2659          let mut search_module = module_;
 2660          let mut index = index;
 2661          let module_path_len = module_path.len();
 2662          let mut closest_private = lp;
 2663  
 2664          // Resolve the module part of the path. This does not involve looking
 2665          // upward though scope chains; we simply resolve names directly in
 2666          // modules as we go.
 2667          while index < module_path_len {
 2668              let name = module_path[index];
 2669              match self.resolve_name_in_module(search_module,
 2670                                                name,
 2671                                                TypeNS,
 2672                                                name_search_type) {
 2673                  Failed => {
 2674                      let segment_name = token::get_ident(name);
 2675                      let module_name = self.module_to_str(search_module);
 2676                      if "???" == module_name {
 2677                          let span = Span {
 2678                              lo: span.lo,
 2679                              hi: span.lo + Pos::from_uint(segment_name.get().len()),
 2680                              expn_info: span.expn_info,
 2681                          };
 2682                          self.resolve_error(span,
 2683                                                format!("unresolved import. maybe \
 2684                                                      a missing `extern crate \
 2685                                                      {}`?",
 2686                                                      segment_name));
 2687                          return Failed;
 2688                      }
 2689                      self.resolve_error(span, format!("unresolved import: could not find `{}` in \
 2690                                                       `{}`.", segment_name, module_name));
 2691                      return Failed;
 2692                  }
 2693                  Indeterminate => {
 2694                      debug!("(resolving module path for import) module \
 2695                              resolution is indeterminate: {}",
 2696                              token::get_ident(name));
 2697                      return Indeterminate;
 2698                  }
 2699                  Success((target, used_proxy)) => {
 2700                      // Check to see whether there are type bindings, and, if
 2701                      // so, whether there is a module within.
 2702                      match *target.bindings.type_def.borrow() {
 2703                          Some(type_def) => {
 2704                              match type_def.module_def {
 2705                                  None => {
 2706                                      // Not a module.
 2707                                      self.resolve_error(span, format!("not a module `{}`",
 2708                                                                   token::get_ident(name)));
 2709                                      return Failed;
 2710                                  }
 2711                                  Some(module_def) => {
 2712                                      // If we're doing the search for an
 2713                                      // import, do not allow traits and impls
 2714                                      // to be selected.
 2715                                      match (name_search_type,
 2716                                             module_def.kind.get()) {
 2717                                          (ImportSearch, TraitModuleKind) |
 2718                                          (ImportSearch, ImplModuleKind) => {
 2719                                              self.resolve_error(
 2720                                                  span,
 2721                                                  "cannot import from a trait \
 2722                                                   or type implementation");
 2723                                              return Failed;
 2724                                          }
 2725                                          (_, _) => {
 2726                                              search_module = module_def;
 2727  
 2728                                              // Keep track of the closest
 2729                                              // private module used when
 2730                                              // resolving this import chain.
 2731                                              if !used_proxy &&
 2732                                                 !search_module.is_public {
 2733                                                  match search_module.def_id
 2734                                                                     .get() {
 2735                                                      Some(did) => {
 2736                                                          closest_private =
 2737                                                              LastMod(DependsOn(did));
 2738                                                      }
 2739                                                      None => {}
 2740                                                  }
 2741                                              }
 2742                                          }
 2743                                      }
 2744                                  }
 2745                              }
 2746                          }
 2747                          None => {
 2748                              // There are no type bindings at all.
 2749                              self.resolve_error(span,
 2750                                                    format!("not a module `{}`",
 2751                                                         token::get_ident(name)));
 2752                              return Failed;
 2753                          }
 2754                      }
 2755                  }
 2756              }
 2757  
 2758              index += 1;
 2759          }
 2760  
 2761          return Success((search_module, closest_private));
 2762      }
 2763  
 2764      /// Attempts to resolve the module part of an import directive or path
 2765      /// rooted at the given module.
 2766      ///
 2767      /// On success, returns the resolved module, and the closest *private*
 2768      /// module found to the destination when resolving this path.
 2769      fn resolve_module_path(&mut self,
 2770                             module_: @Module,
 2771                             module_path: &[Ident],
 2772                             use_lexical_scope: UseLexicalScopeFlag,
 2773                             span: Span,
 2774                             name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 2775                                 -> ResolveResult<(@Module, LastPrivate)> {

 2867      /// Invariant: This must only be called during main resolution, not during
 2868      /// import resolution.
 2869      fn resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(&mut self,
 2870                                       module_: @Module,

 2872                                       namespace: Namespace,

 2874                                       SearchThroughModulesFlag)

 2910                                 namespace);
 2911                      }

 2938              // Go to the next parent.

 2940                  NoParentLink => {

 2962                                      search_module = parent_module_node;
 2963                                  }
 2964                              }

 2966                          SearchThroughModules => {

 2968                          }
 2969                      }
 2970                  }

 2994                      debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) found name \
 2995                              in module, done");

 2997                  }
 2998              }

 3087      /// Resolves a "module prefix". A module prefix is one or both of (a) `self::`;
 3088      /// (b) some chain of `super::`.
 3089      /// grammar: (SELF MOD_SEP ) ? (SUPER MOD_SEP) *
 3090      fn resolve_module_prefix(&mut self,
 3091                               module_: @Module,
 3092                               module_path: &[Ident])
 3093                                   -> ResolveResult<ModulePrefixResult> {
 3094          // Start at the current module if we see `self` or `super`, or at the
 3095          // top of the crate otherwise.
 3096          let mut containing_module;
 3097          let mut i;
 3098          let first_module_path_string = token::get_ident(module_path[0]);
 3099          if "self" == first_module_path_string.get() {
 3100              containing_module =
 3101                  self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent_or_self(module_);
 3102              i = 1;
 3103          } else if "super" == first_module_path_string.get() {
 3104              containing_module =
 3105                  self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent_or_self(module_);
 3106              i = 0;  // We'll handle `super` below.
 3107          } else {
 3108              return Success(NoPrefixFound);
 3109          }
 3110  
 3111          // Now loop through all the `super`s we find.
 3112          while i < module_path.len() {
 3113              let string = token::get_ident(module_path[i]);
 3114              if "super" != string.get() {
 3115                  break
 3116              }
 3117              debug!("(resolving module prefix) resolving `super` at {}",
 3118                     self.module_to_str(containing_module));
 3119              match self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent(containing_module) {
 3120                  None => return Failed,
 3121                  Some(new_module) => {
 3122                      containing_module = new_module;
 3123                      i += 1;
 3124                  }
 3125              }
 3126          }
 3127  
 3128          debug!("(resolving module prefix) finished resolving prefix at {}",
 3129                 self.module_to_str(containing_module));
 3130  
 3131          return Success(PrefixFound(containing_module, i));
 3132      }

 3228                                     "unresolved import");

 3354              if !importresolution.is_public.get() {
 3355                  continue

 3373  
 3374      // AST resolution
 3375      //
 3376      // We maintain a list of value ribs and type ribs.
 3377      //
 3378      // Simultaneously, we keep track of the current position in the module
 3379      // graph in the `current_module` pointer. When we go to resolve a name in
 3380      // the value or type namespaces, we first look through all the ribs and
 3381      // then query the module graph. When we resolve a name in the module
 3382      // namespace, we can skip all the ribs (since nested modules are not
 3383      // allowed within blocks in Rust) and jump straight to the current module
 3384      // graph node.
 3385      //
 3386      // Named implementations are handled separately. When we find a method
 3387      // call, we consult the module node to find all of the implementations in
 3388      // scope. This information is lazily cached in the module node. We then
 3389      // generate a fake "implementation scope" containing all the
 3390      // implementations thus found, for compatibility with old resolve pass.
 3391  
 3392      fn with_scope(&mut self, name: Option<Ident>, f: |&mut Resolver|) {
 3393          let orig_module = self.current_module;
 3394  
 3395          // Move down in the graph.
 3396          match name {
 3397              None => {
 3398                  // Nothing to do.
 3399              }
 3400              Some(name) => {
 3401                  self.populate_module_if_necessary(orig_module);
 3402  
 3403                  match orig_module.children.borrow().find(&name.name) {
 3404                      None => {
 3405                          debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find `{}` in `{}`",
 3406                                 token::get_ident(name),
 3407                                 self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3408                      }
 3409                      Some(name_bindings) => {
 3410                          match (*name_bindings).get_module_if_available() {
 3411                              None => {
 3412                                  debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find module \
 3413                                          for `{}` in `{}`",
 3414                                         token::get_ident(name),
 3415                                         self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3416                              }
 3417                              Some(module_) => {
 3418                                  self.current_module = module_;
 3419                              }
 3420                          }
 3421                      }
 3422                  }
 3423              }
 3424          }
 3425  
 3426          f(self);
 3427  
 3428          self.current_module = orig_module;
 3429      }

 3431      /// Wraps the given definition in the appropriate number of `def_upvar`
 3432      /// wrappers.
 3433      fn upvarify(&mut self,
 3434                      ribs: &mut Vec<@Rib> ,
 3435                      rib_index: uint,
 3436                      def_like: DefLike,
 3437                      span: Span)
 3438                      -> Option<DefLike> {
 3439          let mut def;
 3440          let is_ty_param;
 3441  
 3442          match def_like {
 3443              DlDef(d @ DefLocal(..)) | DlDef(d @ DefUpvar(..)) |
 3444              DlDef(d @ DefArg(..)) | DlDef(d @ DefBinding(..)) => {
 3445                  def = d;
 3446                  is_ty_param = false;
 3447              }
 3448              DlDef(d @ DefTyParam(..)) => {
 3449                  def = d;
 3450                  is_ty_param = true;
 3451              }
 3452              _ => {
 3453                  return Some(def_like);
 3454              }
 3455          }
 3456  
 3457          let mut rib_index = rib_index + 1;
 3458          while rib_index < ribs.len() {
 3459              match ribs.get(rib_index).kind {
 3460                  NormalRibKind => {
 3461                      // Nothing to do. Continue.
 3462                  }
 3463                  FunctionRibKind(function_id, body_id) => {
 3464                      if !is_ty_param {
 3465                          def = DefUpvar(def_id_of_def(def).node,
 3466                                          @def,
 3467                                          function_id,
 3468                                          body_id);
 3469                      }
 3470                  }
 3471                  MethodRibKind(item_id, _) => {
 3472                    // If the def is a ty param, and came from the parent
 3473                    // item, it's ok
 3474                    match def {
 3475                      DefTyParam(did, _) if {
 3476                          self.def_map.borrow().find(&did.node).map(|x| *x)
 3477                              == Some(DefTyParamBinder(item_id))
 3478                      } => {
 3479                        // ok
 3480                      }
 3481                      _ => {
 3482                      if !is_ty_param {
 3483                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3484                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3485                          // report an error.
 3486  
 3487                          self.resolve_error(
 3488                              span,
 3489                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3490                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3491                      } else {
 3492                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3493                          // its scope.
 3494  
 3495                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3496                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3497                                                argument out of scope");
 3498                      }
 3499  
 3500                      return None;
 3501                      }
 3502                    }
 3503                  }
 3504                  OpaqueFunctionRibKind => {
 3505                      if !is_ty_param {
 3506                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3507                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3508                          // report an error.
 3509  
 3510                          self.resolve_error(
 3511                              span,
 3512                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3513                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3514                      } else {
 3515                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3516                          // its scope.
 3517  
 3518                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3519                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3520                                                argument out of scope");
 3521                      }
 3522  
 3523                      return None;
 3524                  }
 3525                  ConstantItemRibKind => {
 3526                      if is_ty_param {
 3527                          // see #9186
 3528                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3529                                                "cannot use an outer type \
 3530                                                 parameter in this context");
 3531                      } else {
 3532                          // Still doesn't deal with upvars
 3533                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3534                                                "attempt to use a non-constant \
 3535                                                 value in a constant");
 3536                      }
 3537  
 3538                  }
 3539              }
 3540  
 3541              rib_index += 1;
 3542          }
 3543  
 3544          return Some(DlDef(def));
 3545      }

 3547      fn search_ribs(&mut self,
 3548                         ribs: &mut Vec<@Rib> ,
 3549                         name: Name,
 3550                         span: Span)
 3551                         -> Option<DefLike> {
 3552          // FIXME #4950: This should not use a while loop.
 3553          // FIXME #4950: Try caching?
 3554  
 3555          let mut i = ribs.len();
 3556          while i != 0 {
 3557              i -= 1;
 3558              let binding_opt = ribs.get(i).bindings.borrow().find_copy(&name);
 3559              match binding_opt {
 3560                  Some(def_like) => {
 3561                      return self.upvarify(ribs, i, def_like, span);
 3562                  }
 3563                  None => {
 3564                      // Continue.
 3565                  }
 3566              }
 3567          }
 3568  
 3569          return None;
 3570      }

 3578      fn resolve_item(&mut self, item: &Item) {
 3579          debug!("(resolving item) resolving {}",
 3580                 token::get_ident(item.ident));
 3581  
 3582          match item.node {
 3583  
 3584              // enum item: resolve all the variants' discrs,
 3585              // then resolve the ty params
 3586              ItemEnum(ref enum_def, ref generics) => {
 3587                  for variant in (*enum_def).variants.iter() {
 3588                      for dis_expr in variant.node.disr_expr.iter() {
 3589                          // resolve the discriminator expr
 3590                          // as a constant
 3591                          self.with_constant_rib(|this| {
 3592                              this.resolve_expr(*dis_expr);
 3593                          });
 3594                      }
 3595                  }
 3596  
 3597                  // n.b. the discr expr gets visted twice.
 3598                  // but maybe it's okay since the first time will signal an
 3599                  // error if there is one? -- tjc
 3600                  self.with_type_parameter_rib(HasTypeParameters(generics,
 3601                                                                 item.id,
 3602                                                                 0,
 3603                                                                 NormalRibKind),
 3604                                               |this| {
 3605                      visit::walk_item(this, item, ());
 3606                  });
 3607              }
 3608  
 3609              ItemTy(_, ref generics) => {
 3610                  self.with_type_parameter_rib(HasTypeParameters(generics,
 3611                                                                 item.id,
 3612                                                                 0,
 3613                                                                 NormalRibKind),
 3614                                               |this| {
 3615                      visit::walk_item(this, item, ());

 3620                        ref implemented_traits,

 3630              ItemTrait(ref generics, ref traits, ref methods) => {

 3633                  self.type_ribs.borrow_mut().push(self_type_rib);
 3634                  // plain insert (no renaming)

 3636                  self_type_rib.bindings.borrow_mut()
 3637                               .insert(name, DlDef(DefSelfTy(item.id)));
 3638  
 3639                  // Create a new rib for the trait-wide type parameters.
 3640                  self.with_type_parameter_rib(HasTypeParameters(generics,
 3641                                                                 item.id,
 3642                                                                 0,
 3643                                                                 NormalRibKind),

 3645                      this.resolve_type_parameters(&generics.ty_params);
 3646  
 3647                      // Resolve derived traits.
 3648                      for trt in traits.iter() {

 3650                      }
 3651  
 3652                      for method in (*methods).iter() {
 3653                          // Create a new rib for the method-specific type
 3654                          // parameters.
 3655                          //

 3659                            ast::Required(ref ty_m) => {

 4062      // build a map from pattern identifiers to binding-info's.

 4065      // user and one 'x' came from the macro.
 4066      fn binding_mode_map(&mut self, pat: @Pat) -> BindingMap {

 4068          pat_bindings(self.def_map, pat, |binding_mode, _id, sp, path| {
 4069              let name = mtwt::resolve(path_to_ident(path));
 4070              result.insert(name,
 4071                            binding_info {span: sp,
 4072                                          binding_mode: binding_mode});
 4073          });

 4075      }
 4076  
 4077      // check that all of the arms in an or-pattern have exactly the
 4078      // same set of bindings, with the same binding modes for each.
 4079      fn check_consistent_bindings(&mut self, arm: &Arm) {
 4080          if arm.pats.len() == 0 {
 4081              return
 4082          }

 4084          for (i, p) in arm.pats.iter().enumerate() {
 4085              let map_i = self.binding_mode_map(*p);
 4086  
 4087              for (&key, &binding_0) in map_0.iter() {
 4088                  match map_i.find(&key) {
 4089                    None => {
 4090                      self.resolve_error(
 4091                          p.span,
 4092                          format!("variable `{}` from pattern \\#1 is \
 4093                                    not bound in pattern \\#{}",
 4094                                  token::get_name(key),
 4095                                  i + 1));
 4096                    }
 4097                    Some(binding_i) => {
 4098                      if binding_0.binding_mode != binding_i.binding_mode {
 4099                          self.resolve_error(
 4100                              binding_i.span,
 4101                              format!("variable `{}` is bound with different \
 4102                                        mode in pattern \\#{} than in pattern \\#1",
 4103                                      token::get_name(key),
 4104                                      i + 1));
 4105                      }
 4106                    }
 4107                  }
 4108              }
 4109  
 4110              for (&key, &binding) in map_i.iter() {
 4111                  if !map_0.contains_key(&key) {
 4112                      self.resolve_error(
 4113                          binding.span,
 4114                          format!("variable `{}` from pattern \\#{} is \
 4115                                    not bound in pattern \\#1",
 4116                                  token::get_name(key),
 4117                                  i + 1));
 4118                  }
 4119              }
 4120          }
 4121      }

 4174              // on whether the path has multiple elements in it or not.
 4175  
 4176              TyPath(ref path, ref bounds, path_id) => {
 4177                  // This is a path in the type namespace. Walk through scopes
 4178                  // looking for it.
 4179                  let mut result_def = None;
 4180  
 4181                  // First, check to see whether the name is a primitive type.
 4182                  if path.segments.len() == 1 {
 4183                      let id = path.segments.last().unwrap().identifier;
 4184  
 4185                      match self.primitive_type_table
 4186                              .primitive_types
 4187                              .find(&id.name) {
 4188  
 4189                          Some(&primitive_type) => {
 4190                              result_def =
 4191                                  Some((DefPrimTy(primitive_type), LastMod(AllPublic)));
 4192  
 4193                              if path.segments
 4194                                     .iter()
 4195                                     .any(|s| !s.lifetimes.is_empty()) {
 4196                                  self.session.span_err(path.span,
 4197                                                        "lifetime parameters \
 4198                                                         are not allowed on \
 4199                                                         this type")
 4200                              } else if path.segments
 4201                                            .iter()
 4202                                            .any(|s| s.types.len() > 0) {
 4203                                  self.session.span_err(path.span,
 4204                                                        "type parameters are \
 4205                                                         not allowed on this \
 4206                                                         type")
 4207                              }
 4208                          }
 4209                          None => {
 4210                              // Continue.
 4211                          }
 4212                      }
 4213                  }
 4214  
 4215                  match result_def {
 4216                      None => {
 4217                          match self.resolve_path(ty.id, path, TypeNS, true) {
 4218                              Some(def) => {
 4219                                  debug!("(resolving type) resolved `{}` to \
 4220                                          type {:?}",
 4221                                         token::get_ident(path.segments
 4222                                                              .last().unwrap()
 4223                                                              .identifier),
 4224                                         def);
 4225                                  result_def = Some(def);
 4226                              }
 4227                              None => {
 4228                                  result_def = None;
 4229                              }
 4230                          }
 4231                      }
 4232                      Some(_) => {}   // Continue.
 4233                  }
 4234  
 4235                  match result_def {
 4236                      Some(def) => {
 4237                          // Write the result into the def map.
 4238                          debug!("(resolving type) writing resolution for `{}` \
 4239                                  (id {})",
 4240                                 self.path_idents_to_str(path),
 4241                                 path_id);
 4242                          self.record_def(path_id, def);
 4243                      }
 4244                      None => {
 4245                          let msg = format!("use of undeclared type name `{}`",
 4246                                            self.path_idents_to_str(path));
 4247                          self.resolve_error(ty.span, msg);
 4248                      }
 4249                  }
 4250  
 4251                  bounds.as_ref().map(|bound_vec| {
 4252                      for bound in bound_vec.iter() {
 4253                          self.resolve_type_parameter_bound(ty.id, bound);
 4254                      }
 4255                  });
 4256              }
 4257  
 4258              TyClosure(c) => {
 4259                  c.bounds.as_ref().map(|bounds| {
 4260                      for bound in bounds.iter() {
 4261                          self.resolve_type_parameter_bound(ty.id, bound);
 4262                      }
 4263                  });
 4264                  visit::walk_ty(self, ty, ());
 4265              }
 4266  
 4267              _ => {
 4268                  // Just resolve embedded types.
 4269                  visit::walk_ty(self, ty, ());
 4270              }
 4271          }
 4272      }

 4274      fn resolve_pattern(&mut self,
 4275                         pattern: @Pat,
 4276                         mode: PatternBindingMode,
 4277                         // Maps idents to the node ID for the (outermost)
 4278                         // pattern that binds them
 4279                         mut bindings_list: Option<&mut HashMap<Name,NodeId>>) {
 4280          let pat_id = pattern.id;
 4281          walk_pat(pattern, |pattern| {
 4282              match pattern.node {
 4283                  PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, _)
 4284                          if !path.global && path.segments.len() == 1 => {
 4285  
 4286                      // The meaning of pat_ident with no type parameters
 4287                      // depends on whether an enum variant or unit-like struct
 4288                      // with that name is in scope. The probing lookup has to
 4289                      // be careful not to emit spurious errors. Only matching
 4290                      // patterns (match) can match nullary variants or
 4291                      // unit-like structs. For binding patterns (let), matching
 4292                      // such a value is simply disallowed (since it's rarely
 4293                      // what you want).
 4294  
 4295                      let ident = path.segments.get(0).identifier;
 4296                      let renamed = mtwt::resolve(ident);
 4297  
 4298                      match self.resolve_bare_identifier_pattern(ident) {
 4299                          FoundStructOrEnumVariant(def, lp)
 4300                                  if mode == RefutableMode => {
 4301                              debug!("(resolving pattern) resolving `{}` to \
 4302                                      struct or enum variant",
 4303                                     token::get_name(renamed));
 4304  
 4305                              self.enforce_default_binding_mode(
 4306                                  pattern,
 4307                                  binding_mode,
 4308                                  "an enum variant");
 4309                              self.record_def(pattern.id, (def, lp));
 4310                          }
 4311                          FoundStructOrEnumVariant(..) => {
 4312                              self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4313                                                    format!("declaration of `{}` \
 4314                                                          shadows an enum \
 4315                                                          variant or unit-like \
 4316                                                          struct in scope",
 4317                                                          token::get_name(renamed)));
 4318                          }
 4319                          FoundConst(def, lp) if mode == RefutableMode => {
 4320                              debug!("(resolving pattern) resolving `{}` to \
 4321                                      constant",
 4322                                     token::get_name(renamed));
 4323  
 4324                              self.enforce_default_binding_mode(
 4325                                  pattern,
 4326                                  binding_mode,
 4327                                  "a constant");
 4328                              self.record_def(pattern.id, (def, lp));
 4329                          }
 4330                          FoundConst(..) => {
 4331                              self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4332                                                    "only irrefutable patterns \
 4333                                                     allowed here");
 4334                          }
 4335                          BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved => {
 4336                              debug!("(resolving pattern) binding `{}`",
 4337                                     token::get_name(renamed));
 4338  
 4339                              let def = match mode {
 4340                                  RefutableMode => {
 4341                                      // For pattern arms, we must use
 4342                                      // `def_binding` definitions.
 4343  
 4344                                      DefBinding(pattern.id, binding_mode)
 4345                                  }
 4346                                  LocalIrrefutableMode => {
 4347                                      // But for locals, we use `def_local`.
 4348                                      DefLocal(pattern.id, binding_mode)
 4349                                  }
 4350                                  ArgumentIrrefutableMode => {
 4351                                      // And for function arguments, `def_arg`.
 4352                                      DefArg(pattern.id, binding_mode)
 4353                                  }
 4354                              };
 4355  
 4356                              // Record the definition so that later passes
 4357                              // will be able to distinguish variants from
 4358                              // locals in patterns.
 4359  
 4360                              self.record_def(pattern.id, (def, LastMod(AllPublic)));
 4361  
 4362                              // Add the binding to the local ribs, if it
 4363                              // doesn't already exist in the bindings list. (We
 4364                              // must not add it if it's in the bindings list
 4365                              // because that breaks the assumptions later
 4366                              // passes make about or-patterns.)
 4367  
 4368                              match bindings_list {
 4369                                  Some(ref mut bindings_list)
 4370                                  if !bindings_list.contains_key(&renamed) => {
 4371                                      let this = &mut *self;
 4372                                      let value_ribs = this.value_ribs.borrow();
 4373                                      let length = value_ribs.len();
 4374                                      let last_rib = value_ribs.get(
 4375                                          length - 1);
 4376                                      last_rib.bindings.borrow_mut()
 4377                                              .insert(renamed, DlDef(def));
 4378                                      bindings_list.insert(renamed, pat_id);
 4379                                  }
 4380                                  Some(ref mut b) => {
 4381                                    if b.find(&renamed) == Some(&pat_id) {
 4382                                        // Then this is a duplicate variable
 4383                                        // in the same disjunct, which is an
 4384                                        // error
 4385                                       self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4386                                         format!("identifier `{}` is bound more \
 4387                                               than once in the same pattern",
 4388                                              path_to_str(path)));
 4389                                    }
 4390                                    // Not bound in the same pattern: do nothing
 4391                                  }
 4392                                  None => {
 4393                                      let this = &mut *self;
 4394                                      {
 4395                                          let value_ribs = this.value_ribs.borrow();
 4396                                          let length = value_ribs.len();
 4397                                          let last_rib = value_ribs.get(
 4398                                                  length - 1);
 4399                                          last_rib.bindings.borrow_mut()
 4400                                                  .insert(renamed, DlDef(def));
 4401                                      }
 4402                                  }
 4403                              }
 4404                          }
 4405                      }
 4406  
 4407                      // Check the types in the path pattern.
 4408                      for &ty in path.segments
 4409                                    .iter()
 4410                                    .flat_map(|seg| seg.types.iter()) {
 4411                          self.resolve_type(ty);
 4412                      }
 4413                  }

 4415                  PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, _) => {

 4525      fn resolve_bare_identifier_pattern(&mut self, name: Ident)
 4526                                             ->
 4527                                             BareIdentifierPatternResolution {
 4528          match self.resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(self.current_module,
 4529                                                   name,
 4530                                                   ValueNS,
 4531                                                   SearchThroughModules) {
 4532              Success((target, _)) => {
 4533                  debug!("(resolve bare identifier pattern) succeeded in \
 4534                           finding {} at {:?}",
 4535                          token::get_ident(name),
 4536                          target.bindings.value_def.borrow());
 4537                  match *target.bindings.value_def.borrow() {
 4538                      None => {
 4539                          fail!("resolved name in the value namespace to a \
 4540                                set of name bindings with no def?!");
 4541                      }
 4542                      Some(def) => {
 4543                          // For the two success cases, this lookup can be
 4544                          // considered as not having a private component because
 4545                          // the lookup happened only within the current module.
 4546                          match def.def {
 4547                              def @ DefVariant(..) | def @ DefStruct(..) => {
 4548                                  return FoundStructOrEnumVariant(def, LastMod(AllPublic));
 4549                              }
 4550                              def @ DefStatic(_, false) => {
 4551                                  return FoundConst(def, LastMod(AllPublic));
 4552                              }
 4553                              _ => {
 4554                                  return BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved;
 4555                              }
 4556                          }
 4557                      }
 4558                  }
 4559              }
 4560  
 4561              Indeterminate => {
 4562                  fail!("unexpected indeterminate result");
 4563              }
 4564  
 4565              Failed => {
 4566                  debug!("(resolve bare identifier pattern) failed to find {}",
 4567                          token::get_ident(name));
 4568                  return BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved;
 4569              }
 4570          }
 4571      }

 4573      /// If `check_ribs` is true, checks the local definitions first; i.e.
 4574      /// doesn't skip straight to the containing module.
 4575      fn resolve_path(&mut self,
 4576                      id: NodeId,
 4577                      path: &Path,
 4578                      namespace: Namespace,
 4579                      check_ribs: bool) -> Option<(Def, LastPrivate)> {
 4580          // First, resolve the types.
 4581          for &ty in path.segments.iter().flat_map(|s| s.types.iter()) {
 4582              self.resolve_type(ty);
 4583          }
 4584  
 4585          if path.global {
 4586              return self.resolve_crate_relative_path(path, namespace);
 4587          }
 4588  
 4589          let unqualified_def =
 4590                  self.resolve_identifier(path.segments
 4591                                              .last().unwrap()
 4592                                              .identifier,
 4593                                          namespace,
 4594                                          check_ribs,
 4595                                          path.span);
 4596  
 4597          if path.segments.len() > 1 {
 4598              let def = self.resolve_module_relative_path(path, namespace);
 4599              match (def, unqualified_def) {
 4600                  (Some((d, _)), Some((ud, _))) if d == ud => {
 4601                      self.session.add_lint(UnnecessaryQualification,
 4602                                            id,
 4603                                            path.span,
 4604                                            ~"unnecessary qualification");
 4605                  }
 4606                  _ => ()
 4607              }
 4608  
 4609              return def;
 4610          }
 4611  
 4612          return unqualified_def;
 4613      }

 4615      // resolve a single identifier (used as a varref)
 4616      fn resolve_identifier(&mut self,

 4618                                namespace: Namespace,
 4619                                check_ribs: bool,
 4620                                span: Span)

 4624                                                        namespace,

 4630                      // Continue.

 4915      fn find_best_match_for_name(&mut self, name: &str, max_distance: uint)
 4916                                  -> Option<~str> {
 4917          let this = &mut *self;
 4918  
 4919          let mut maybes: Vec<token::InternedString> = Vec::new();
 4920          let mut values: Vec<uint> = Vec::new();
 4921  
 4922          let mut j = this.value_ribs.borrow().len();
 4923          while j != 0 {
 4924              j -= 1;
 4925              let value_ribs = this.value_ribs.borrow();
 4926              let bindings = value_ribs.get(j).bindings.borrow();
 4927              for (&k, _) in bindings.iter() {
 4928                  maybes.push(token::get_name(k));
 4929                  values.push(uint::MAX);
 4930              }
 4931          }
 4932  
 4933          let mut smallest = 0;
 4934          for (i, other) in maybes.iter().enumerate() {
 4935              *values.get_mut(i) = name.lev_distance(other.get());
 4936  
 4937              if *values.get(i) <= *values.get(smallest) {
 4938                  smallest = i;
 4939              }
 4940          }
 4941  
 4942          if values.len() > 0 &&
 4943              *values.get(smallest) != uint::MAX &&
 4944              *values.get(smallest) < name.len() + 2 &&
 4945              *values.get(smallest) <= max_distance &&
 4946              name != maybes.get(smallest).get() {
 4947  
 4948              Some(maybes.get(smallest).get().to_str())
 4949  
 4950          } else {
 4951              None
 4952          }
 4953      }
